T1  - MODELING MOVEMENTS IN INDIVIDUAL CONSUMPTION: A TIME-SERIES ANALYSIS OF GROUPED DATA
AU  - Attanasio, Orazio P.
AU  - Borella, Margherita
Y1  - 2014/11/01
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2014/11/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12079
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
JA  - International Economic Review
SP  - 959
EP  - 991
VL  - 55
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12079
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We characterize the time-series properties of group-level consumption, income, and interest rates using microdata. We relate the coefficients of moving average representations to structural parameters of theoretical models of consumption behavior. Using long time series of cross sections to construct synthetic panel data for the United Kingdom, we find that for high-educated individuals the Euler equation restrictions are not rejected, the elasticity of intertemporal substitution is higher than one, and there is evidence of ?excess smoothness? of consumption. Low-educated individuals, conversely, exhibit excess sensitivity of consumption to past income, and the elasticity of intertemporal substitution is not statistically different from zero.
ER  - 

