T1  - DIRECTED SEARCH AND THE BERTRAND PARADOX
AU  - Geromichalos, Athanasios
Y1  - 2014/11/01
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2014/11/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12082
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
JA  - International Economic Review
SP  - 1043
EP  - 1065
VL  - 55
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12082
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - I study a directed search model of oligopolistic competition, extended to incorporate general capacity constraints, congestion effects, and pricing based on ex post demand. In the presence of any one of these ingredients, the Bertrand paradox fails to hold. Hence, despite the emphasis that has been placed by the literature on sellers' capacity constraints as a resolution to the paradox, the existence of such constraints is only a subcase of a general class of environments where the paradox fails. Specifically, Bertrand's paradox will not arise whenever the buyers' expected utility from visiting a seller is decreasing in that seller's realized demand.
ER  - 

